Section: science
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://github.com/arohl/gdis
Description: GTK/OpenGL editor and viewer for atomistic structures
 GDIS is a desktop application for building, visualizing, and analyzing
 atomistic and crystallographic structures.
 .
 This packaging refresh targets the renewed GTK4 backend so the package no
 longer depends on the obsolete GTK2 and gtkglext stack that led to removal
 from Debian unstable. The GTK4 port is still a modernization branch, but it
 already restores practical molecule rendering, selection overlays,
 diffraction graphs, and iso-surface workflows.
